cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
title: "LLM x SFM Safety Evaluation: refusal calibration on the science-foundation-model interpretation channel"
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Kim
    given-names: JangKeun
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0520-3703"
    affiliation: "Mason Lab, Weill Cornell Medicine"
year: 2026
repository-code: "https://github.com/jang1563/llm-sfm-safety-eval"
abstract: >-
  An evaluation of how deployed Claude models behave on the channel where a
  language model interprets the output of a specialist science foundation model.
  Four findings document discontinuous cross-version refusal swings, a calibration
  gradient from genuine sequence recognition to context-keyword over-refusal, a
  managed-access (not scale-driven) safety layer, and a keyword-triggered tool-mode
  surface. Defensive and aggregate-only.
keywords:
  - AI safety
  - biosecurity
  - science foundation models
  - refusal calibration
  - frontier model evaluation
  - Claude
